## Responsive Design (Desktop-First)

### Breakpoints

```
Default (no prefix): 1280px and up (desktop) ← PRIMARY TARGET
lg:  1024px  - Laptops / small desktops
md:  768px   - Tablets (landscape)
sm:  640px   - Large mobile phones
```

### Desktop-First Approach

```html
<!-- Default = Desktop, scale down for smaller screens -->

<!-- Grid: 4 columns → 3 → 2 → 1 -->
<div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-8 
            lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-6
            md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-4
            sm:grid-cols-1 sm:gap-2">
  <div>Item 1</div>
  <div>Item 2</div>
  <div>Item 3</div>
  <div>Item 4</div>
</div>

<!-- Typography: Scale down -->
<h1 class="text-6xl font-bold 
           lg:text-5xl
           md:text-4xl
           sm:text-3xl">
  Page Title
</h1>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed
          md:text-base md:leading-normal
          sm:text-sm sm:leading-snug">
  Body text scales down for smaller screens.
</p>

<!-- Spacing: Scale down -->
<div class="p-8 m-4 space-y-6
            md:p-6 md:m-3 md:space-y-4
            sm:p-4 sm:m-2 sm:space-y-2">
  Content with scaled spacing
</div>

<!-- Layout: Change direction -->
<div class="flex flex-row gap-6
            md:flex-col md:gap-4">
  <aside class="w-64 md:w-full">Sidebar</aside>
  <main class="flex-1">Main Content</main>
</div>
```

### Show/Hide by Screen Size

```html
<!-- Visible only on desktop (>768px) -->
<div class="block md:hidden">
  Desktop navigation
</div>

<!-- Visible only on tablet/mobile (≤768px) -->
<div class="hidden md:block">
  Mobile navigation
</div>

<!-- Visible only on mobile (≤640px) -->
<div class="hidden sm:block md:hidden">
  Mobile-specific content
</div>
```

